THE HIGH CHAPARRAL

15. The Terrorist    12/17/1967
Manolito frees his old friend Santos from a Mexican jail, where he has been imprisoned by the French as a terrorist for Juarez. Santos and his sister, Pilar, are taken to the Cannon Ranch where Victoria arranges for Juarez to plan an invasion of Mexico. Manolito learns Santos has turned traitor and plans to conquer French-ruled Mexico himself. Before Manolito can warn his friends, Santos&#039;s followers take over the ranch and prepare to kill the exiled president of Mexico upon his arrival.

Writer: William F. Leicester
Director: Ralph Senensky
Guest star: Paul Bryar (Sgt. Tousseau), John Cardos (Third Bandit), Gil Frye (Soldier), Walt La Rue (Second Bandit), Andrew Orapeza (Farmer), Lalo Rios (First Bandit), Ned Romero (Rinaldo), Pilar Seurat (Pilar Castaneda), Henry Silva (Santos Castaneda)
